üìù Restart Environment: Semantic Scholar + 3D Papers Viewer

1. Activate Python Environment

    cd path/to/your/project
    source venv/bin/activate         # for Unix/macOS
    .\venv\Scripts\activate          # for Windows

2. Start Local LLM (Ollama)

    ollama run mistral

   Or keep Ollama running in background:

    ollama serve &

3. Run Backend Script

    python summarize_semantic_scholar.py

   Generates nodes.json and edges.json and copies them to the frontend.

4. Start Frontend (React 3D Viewer)

    cd ../arxiv-3d-frontend
    npm install         # only needed once
    npm run dev         # or: npm start

5. Open in Browser

    http://localhost:3000

6. (Optional) Rebuild or Debug

    - Check for errors in summarize_semantic_scholar.py output.
    - Ensure nodes.json and edges.json are present in arxiv-3d-frontend/public/
